projectelo.tip_message.title: Tips!
projectelo.tip_message.0: Did you know? "MCSR" stands for Minecraft Speedrunning.
projectelo.tip_message.1: Don't forget to join our Discord server!
projectelo.tip_message.2: All players in a match will have the same RNG... except for the dragon.
projectelo.tip_message.3: Are you enjoying the game? Please support us in the store! :)
projectelo.tip_message.5: When pillaring up using alternating slabs, 6 total logs can produce 48 blocks of height.
projectelo.tip_message.7: If you are new to Ranked, it may be helpful to practice first ;)
projectelo.tip_message.9: The Ender Dragon’s chance to fireball the player at certain intervals is 50% when the player is close to the End fountain and about 10% when far away.
projectelo.tip_message.10: Have any feedback? Feel free to post it in our Discord server!
projectelo.tip_message.11: Fall damage is reduced by 80% when landing on a haybale and 50% when landing on a bed.
projectelo.tip_message.12: Cobblestone takes 1.5 seconds to break with a wooden pickaxe, while a stone pickaxe only takes 1.15 seconds.
projectelo.tip_message.13: Gravel takes 0.25 seconds to mine with a stone shovel and 0.15 seconds with both iron and diamond shovels.
projectelo.tip_message.14: Strongholds attempt to avoid generating in oceans and swamps, and are occasionally pushed to other biomes nearby.
projectelo.tip_message.15: Most hostile mobs have a chance to despawn if more than 32 blocks away from a player and are forced to despawn when over 128 blocks away.
projectelo.tip_message.16: Dolphin’s Grace allows the player to swim at a speed of 9.8 blocks per second, while boating gives a speed of 8 blocks per second.
projectelo.tip_message.17: Unlike bed and respawn anchor explosions, TNT drops all destroyed blocks and does not generate fire.
projectelo.tip_message.18: Increasing the game's difficulty will increase the rate of fire spreading, but not the blocks initially catching on fire.
projectelo.tip_message.19: Combining dirt and gravel to make coarse dirt is a great way to turn gravity blocks into non-gravity ones.
projectelo.tip_message.20: At the top of desert pyramids, terracotta has a default breaking time of 6.25 seconds, while sandstone only takes 4 seconds.
projectelo.tip_message.21: Boats will prevent fall damage unless you fall exactly 12, 13, 49, 51, 111, 114, 198, 202, 310, or 315 blocks.
projectelo.tip_message.22: Certain items create air pockets for players to breathe underwater, including doors, pressure plates, fence gates, beds, and sugar cane.
projectelo.tip_message.23: Excess early iron can be crafted into shears for collecting leaves, doors for breathing underwater, or iron bars for pillaring up.
projectelo.tip_message.24: Shields only prevent damage from the front of the player’s hitbox, meaning attacks from above or below will still hit.
projectelo.tip_message.25: Piglins become angered up to 16 blocks away from the player's position when mining a block of gold or a chest.
projectelo.tip_message.26: When angered, full-health Piglins are willing to fall 5 blocks on Easy, 9 blocks on Medium, and 13 blocks on Hard difficulty.
projectelo.tip_message.27: With 3 emeralds, you can trade for a bucket of cod with a fisherman, 18 bread with a farmer, or an iron axe with a weaponsmith.
projectelo.tip_message.28: Some mobs reduce the spawn rate of identical mobs nearby, including skeletons in soul sand valley biomes and Endermen in warped forests.
projectelo.tip_message.29: Soul sand blocks have a height of 0.875, compared to the 1 of most other blocks, including soul soil.
projectelo.tip_message.30: Piglins are naturally aggressive towards Wither Skeletons but not Hoglins that naturally spawn in bastions.
projectelo.tip_message.31: Mobs like Piglins and Wither Skeletons will try to avoid pathing onto lava, fire, and magma blocks.
projectelo.tip_message.32: Wood from crimson and warped forest trees can be crafted into most items regular wood can, except for boats.
projectelo.tip_message.33: The lodestone chest in Bridge bastions cannot contain obsidian but can contain iron.
projectelo.tip_message.34: Piglins can still remain angered for about 1-2 seconds after losing line of sight to players opening chests.
projectelo.tip_message.35: Crafting spectral arrows requires lots of glowstone but can effectively double your arrow count.
projectelo.tip_message.36: Ghast fireballs have an explosion power of 1, TNT is 4, and beds and respawn anchors are 5.
projectelo.tip_message.37: If an Eye of Ender is right-clicked while looking at a filled End Portal Frame block, it will not be thrown.
projectelo.tip_message.38: Each End Portal Frame block has a 10% chance of being already filled upon generation.
projectelo.tip_message.39: End Portal rooms can only generate at least 7 rooms away from the stronghold's starter staircase.
projectelo.tip_message.40: End Portal rooms, unlike other stronghold rooms, cannot be overwritten by natural features like ravines.
projectelo.tip_message.41: Each End island will generate the same set of 10 obsidian pillars, just in different configurations.
projectelo.tip_message.42: The Ender Dragon’s chance of perching at certain intervals starts at 1 in 13 but becomes 1 in 3 when all 10 End Crystals are destroyed.
projectelo.tip_message.43: The Ender Dragon will fireball the player when an End Crystal is destroyed, regardless of the source of damage.
projectelo.tip_message.44: The intended bastion will always contain at least 3 iron and 5 obsidian in chests.
projectelo.tip_message.45: Seed type distributions are determined by your rank, with low Elo runners having easier seeds on average.
projectelo.tip_message.46: The intended fortress will always generate within 17 chunks of the bastion. You can use your pie chart to find the approximate direction.
projectelo.tip_message.47: There are 5 ranks ranging from 0 to 2000 Elo: Coal, Iron, Gold, Emerald, and Diamond. Each rank has 3 tiers, with 3 being the highest.
